2. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): Active learning is a subfield of AI, and the paper proposes a new algorithm in this area. 
3. cs.CV (Computer Vision): Nearest neighbor classifiers are commonly used in computer vision tasks, and the paper proposes an active learning algorithm for this type of classifier. 
4. cs.CL (Computation and Language): Active learning can be used for natural language processing tasks, and the paper proposes a general algorithm for metric spaces, which can include text data. 
5. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper proposes a new sample compression scheme and active model-selection procedure, which are relevant to data structures and algorithms.
